primary_diagnosis.justification: Based on the documented history of recurrent episodes and the denial of manic/hypomanic history, F33 is appropriate. The recent initiation of *Sertraline* 4 weeks ago, indicating symptoms causing impairment requiring treatment, aligns with an ongoing Moderate Major Depressive Episode.
dsm_criteria_met: Meets criteria for Major Depressive Episode (MDE)
Symptoms present for > 2 weeks, causing distress/impairment
History confirms multiple prior episodes (Recurrent specifier met)

ruled_out.reason: Patient history explicitly suggests Recurrent MDD, ruling out a single episode presentation.
Clinical Entity Agent confirms patient denies any history of manic or hypomanic episodes.
